Say not ‘to-morrow’ or ‘the day after to-morrow'; for those that perished,
perished because they abode always in their hopes, until the truth came upon
them suddenly in their heedlessness, and wilful as they were they were
carried to their dark, narrow graves, abandoned by all their kith and kin.
